 # Changelog
 
+## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S1-P03-T019 (content QA + single retry + factsheet fallback)
+
+- Nineteenth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S1-P03), one task per run. Goal: on a generation failure, prefer to say less rather than publish template garbage. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; reuses the T018 render payload, no worker/D1 change and no model call (a self-test stub simulates generation). Deliverable under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: tools/content_qa.py (five QA checks -- language large-English, empty, duplicate, unsupported (a claim without an evidence locator), and template boilerplate -- plus publish() with at most one retry and fallback() which quarantines L2 and publishes only the fact card L0/L1 + raw evidence L3). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S1-P03-T019/test-results/qa_tests.txt) at 5/5 PASS: injecting a model timeout falls back after at most one retry (initial + 1) to publish_mode fact_card_and_raw_only; injecting template garbage or a missing-field stub fails QA and falls back; a duplicate L2 falls back; a valid generation publishes in full in a single attempt; and the baseline payload has no unsupported claims. This seals the english_direct_output/template defects on the publish path. Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls at most 2 per item (controlled by publish()). Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S1-P03-T018 (L0-L3 人话版 content contract + evidence locator)
 
 - Eighteenth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S1-P03), one task per run. Goal: output the 15-second, 2-minute, deep, and raw-evidence layers and distinguish fact/interpretation/inference. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; reuses the T016/T017 sample, no worker/D1 change and no model call. Per the Owner directive of 2026-07-16 the L2 deep layer requires a model and is kept provisional_pending_model (not generated, not fabricated). Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: schemas/content_contract.schema.json (L0 15s / L1 2min / L2 deep / L3 raw-evidence, with claim fact/interpretation/inference and an evidence locator), tools/build_render_payload.py (deterministic builder: L0/L1 are Chinese fact layers with a locator on every claim, the raw possibly-English abstract goes ONLY into a labeled L3, L2 is provisional_pending_model), BOARD_PROMPTS.md (per-board L2 prompts distinguishing fact/interpretation/inference and citing locators), and render_payload_sample.json (200 payloads). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S1-P03-T018/test-results/content_tests.txt): the 200-payload schema validation PASSES; zero English abstracts leak into L0/L1 (all raw English is routed to the labeled L3, so the Chinese UI has no unexplained large English -- the one Chinese board3 title==summary case is Chinese, not English); every key number/date/result is 100% locatable (all 1479 L0/L1 claims carry an evidence locator and the 479 key facts date/DOI/units/doc_number are 479/479 located); and the build is deterministic (byte-identical re-build). This fixes the T017 english_direct_output defect (113/200) at the contract level and answers FACT-002 and the v1.1 fact/interpretation/inference requirement. Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0 (L2 not generated). Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
